HEADWORD: Romajikai
<hw>Ro"ma*ji*ka`i</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Jap.
<ets>r⟦omac⟧majikai</ets>, Roman character association.]</ety> <def>An
association, including both Japanese and Europeans, having for its
object the changing of the Japanese method of writing by substituting
Roman letters for Japanese characters. Laso known as <altname>Hyojun
Romajikai</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

